                           Monthly Treasury Statement

   Updated January 22, 2002

   CURRENT ISSUE

   December 2001:

   PDF PDF File Format (377 KB)

   ASCII Text File (616 KB)

   The Monthly Treasury Statement of Receipts and Outlays of the United
   States Government (MTS) summarizes the financial activities of the
   Federal Government and off-budget Federal entities in accordance with
   the Budget of the U.S. Government. It presents receipts and outlays,
   the surplus or deficit, and means of financing on a modified cash
   basis. The MTS is prepared by the Financial Management Service,
   Department of the Treasury, and after approval by the Fiscal Assistant
   Secretary of the Treasury, the MTS is normally released on the 14th
   workday of the month following the reporting month. The publication is
   based on data provided by Federal entities, disbursing officers, and
   Federal Reserve banks.

   Subscribe to FMS E-mail notification service.

   Note: ASCII files do not contain graphics

